header.gameNote: NIT CONSOLATION AT BOWLING GREEN KY

article.headline: Coastal Carolina 77, Indiana St. 62
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. -- Joseph Harris scored 22 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead Coastal Carolina past Indiana State 77-62 on Monday night. The Chanticleers (4-1) led 34-33 at halftime, before opening the second half on an 18-6 run. Kierre Greenwood's layup capped the run for a 52-39 Coastal Carolina lead with 13:19 left in the NIT Season Tip-off. The Chanticleers jumped out to a 17-12 lead, but the Sycamores (3-2) went on a 13-6 run to take a 25-23 lead with 3:59 left in the first half on a jump shot by Jordan Printy. Coastal Carolina reclaimed the lead for good on a Logan Johnson 3-pointer with 2:15 left before halftime for a 30-28 advantage. Greenwood finished with 17 points, and Mario Edwards and Chad Gray added 14 each for the Chanticleers, who start 4-1 for the first time since the 1993-94 season. Dwayne Lathan scored 14 points for Indiana State.
